---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteSections } from "../data/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Astro site bootstrap"
  description="A first-pass Astro shell for the F-flat-minor website, styled after the current web app."
  theme="home"
  activePath="/"
>
  <section class="hero-grid">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">f-flat-minor / web2</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Bring the F♭m site into Astro without losing its voice.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lede">
        This first step sets up Astro layouts, routes, and shared styling inspired by the current browser
        app. The interactive playground, REPL, codettas, and tutorials stay in <code>/web</code> for now.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button-link primary" href="/playground/">Browse the new routes</a>
        <a class="button-link secondary" href="/help/">See the easiest migration target</a>
      </div>
      <div class="migration-note">
        <p>
          The intent here is structure first: Astro owns navigation, page layout, and static content framing;
          the existing client-side tools can be embedded later.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="hero-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">What ships now</p>
      <h2>Static shell, ready for gradual migration.</h2>
      <ol class="stack">
        <li><strong>Shared layout</strong> for nav, branding, and page chrome</li>
        <li><strong>Dedicated routes</strong> for the main tool areas</li>
        <li><strong>Global styling</strong> lifted from the current warm glassmorphism palette</li>
        <li><strong>Room to embed</strong> the current interactive surfaces later</li>
      </ol>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section grid feature-grid" aria-label="Site sections">
    {
      siteSections.map((section) => (
        <article class="feature-card">
          <p class="eyebrow">{section.eyebrow}</p>
          <h3>{section.title}</h3>
          <p>{section.summary}</p>
          <footer>
            <a class="inline-link" href={`/${section.slug}/`}>
              Open the {section.title.toLowerCase()} route
            </a>
          </footer>
        </article>
      ))
    }
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
